=== Software ===
Portage knows the global USE flag ''udisks'' for enabling support for udisks in other packages. Enabling this USE flag will pull in {{Package|sys-fs/udisks}} automatically (default for ''desktop'' [[profile]]s):
{{File|/etc/portage/make.conf||<pre>
USE="... udisks ..."
</pre>}}
The USE flags of udisks1 are:
{{USEflag|package=sys-fs/udisks
|debug
|nls+yes
|remote-access
}}

The USE flags of udisks2 are:
{{USEflag|package=sys-fs/udisks
|crypt+yes
|debug
|gptfdisk+yes
|introspection+yes
|systemd
}}

After setting this you want to update your system so the changes take effect:
{{RootCmd|emerge --ask --changed-use --deep world}}

== Addon software ==
* {{Package|sys-apps/gnome-disk-utility}} - [[GNOME]] program to partition, configure and monitor storage devices.
* {{Package|sys-fs/udiskie}} - Automatic mount of drives.
* {{Package|sys-fs/udisks-glue}} - Run actions on udisks events.

== Configuration ==
udisks uses [[polkit]] to handle permissions.

== Usage ==
Some useful commands are:
* '''upower --enumerate''' - Lists all storage devices.
* '''upower --monitor''' - Monitor udisks.
* '''upower --monitor-details''' - Monitor udisks with more details.
* '''upower --inhibit-polling /dev/DEVICEFILE''' - Disable polling on the given device.

